---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "Blog - All Posts";
const description = "All blog posts about technology, programming, and life experiences.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="mb-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">All Blog Posts</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-600">
      Thoughts, tutorials, and deep dives into technology, programming, and life.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="space-y-8">
    <!-- Blog Post 1 -->
    <article class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
      <div class="flex items-center text-sm text-gray-500 mb-3">
        <time datetime="2025-08-24">August 24, 2025</time>
        <span class="mx-2">•</span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
        <a href="/blog/building-with-astro" class="hover:text-blue-600">Building a Modern Blog with Astro and Tailwind</a>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
        Exploring the power of Astro for building fast, content-focused websites with modern tooling and excellent developer experience. We'll cover setting up Tailwind CSS, creating reusable layouts, and optimizing for performance.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        <span class="inline-block bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">Astro</span>
        <span class="inline-block bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">Tailwind</span>
        <span class="inline-block bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">Web Dev</span>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Blog Post 2 -->
    <article class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
      <div class="flex items-center text-sm text-gray-500 mb-3">
        <time datetime="2025-08-23">August 23, 2025</time>
        <span class="mx-2">•</span>
        <span>7 min read</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
        <a href="/blog/jupyter-notebooks-web" class="hover:text-blue-600">Integrating Jupyter Notebooks in Web Applications</a>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
        How to seamlessly embed and render Jupyter notebooks in web applications for better data science communication. We'll explore nbconvert, custom renderers, and interactive widgets that work in production.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        <span class="inline-block bg-orange-100 text-orange-800 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">Jupyter</span>
        <span class="inline-block bg-red-100 text-red-800 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">Data Science</span>
        <span class="inline-block bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-800 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">Python</span>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Blog Post 3 -->
    <article class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
      <div class="flex items-center text-sm text-gray-500 mb-3">
        <time datetime="2025-08-22">August 22, 2025</time>
        <span class="mx-2">•</span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
        <a href="/blog/mathematical-notation-web" class="hover:text-blue-600">Beautiful Mathematical Notation on the Web</a>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
        Implementing LaTeX-style mathematical equations in web content using KaTeX and modern markdown processors. Learn how to render complex formulas, inline equations, and interactive mathematical content.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        <span class="inline-block bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-800 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">Math</span>
        <span class="inline-block bg-pink-100 text-pink-800 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">LaTeX</span>
        <span class="inline-block bg-cyan-100 text-cyan-800 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">KaTeX</span>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Blog Post 4 -->
    <article class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
      <div class="flex items-center text-sm text-gray-500 mb-3">
        <time datetime="2025-08-21">August 21, 2025</time>
        <span class="mx-2">•</span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
        <a href="/blog/marimo-reactive-notebooks" class="hover:text-blue-600">Reactive Notebooks with Marimo</a>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
        Discover Marimo, a new approach to Python notebooks that brings reactivity and deterministic execution. Perfect for data analysis, machine learning prototyping, and interactive documentation.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        <span class="inline-block bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-800 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">Marimo</span>
        <span class="inline-block bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-800 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">Python</span>
        <span class="inline-block bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">Notebooks</span>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>

  <!-- Pagination -->
  <nav class="flex justify-center mt-12" aria-label="Pagination">
    <div class="flex space-x-2">
      <span class="px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-500 bg-gray-100 rounded-md">Previous</span>
      <span class="px-3 py-2 text-sm bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-md">1</span>
      <a href="/blog/page/2" class="px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded-md hover:bg-gray-50">2</a>
      <a href="/blog/page/3" class="px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded-md hover:bg-gray-50">3</a>
      <a href="/blog/page/2" class="px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded-md hover:bg-gray-50">Next</a>
    </div>
  </nav>
</BaseLayout>
